# skill-execution-guardrails

MODE: ALWAYS_ON
META_SKILLS (*-meta): ANALYZE_ONLY NO_EDITS NO_CMDS
EXEC_SKILLS (*-execution): IMPLEMENT_OR_VERIFY per contract

OUT_FORMAT: terse structured default; verbose only if user asks or context requires
INTENT: classify prompt as question|plan|implement|debug|review|git|docs
COMPLEXITY: classify as simple|moderate|high
ROUTING: simple+clear ask => skip skill; execute directly
ROUTING: ambiguous/high-risk/multi-step => prefer matching *-meta before edits
ROUTING: implement/debug/verify/commit asks => prefer matching *-execution skill
ROUTING: post-implementation doc/status/changelog updates => prefer core-doc-sync-after-implementation-execution
ROUTING: Jira import/sync from references/worklogs => prefer core-atlassian-jira-sync-execution
FALLBACK: if no relevant skill or prompt is trivial, proceed without skill

DEBUG: one minimal fix per iteration + hypothesis + verification record
VERIFY: never claim done without required checks
GIT: commit only on explicit user request
SKILL_CREATOR: only on explicit request to create/edit/package skill